      "side": 1,
      "message": "Good point, currently they are not, compare https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:third_party/freetype/src/src/sfnt/ttcolr.c;l\u003d742;drc\u003d25b97f298830b78a443fd7cdfd0b3e190817d1dd?q\u003dttcolr.c - just reading them from the color stops of a color line. But it\u0027s good idea to sanitize them on the FreeType side. \n\nThey can\u0027t conveniently be sanitized here as the FT_Color* palette array is passed without a known size. As this CL does not intend to change any functionality but just restructure to code, I added a TODO for myself to validate the palette index values on the FreeType side. There I believe we do have access to CPAL and can check them before returning.\n\nAlso the foreground value needs to be handled here, but I think that applies to CORLv0 in Skia as well. Again, I may want to claim that this is unrelated to this CL.",
